  "title": "Engineering Manager (Medical Device)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>In charge of driving  the Engineering team in executing improvement initiatives to achieve cost savings and productivity targets</li><li>Responsible in ensuring Overall Equipment Effectiveness meets targeted performance level.</li><li>In charge of overseeing and managing facilities maintenance activities and troubleshoot equipment issues to ensure uninterrupted operations.</li><li>Responsible in leading and taking ownership of in-house and automation machines which include software development, covering concept development, design, budgeting, testing, commissioning, upgrades, and continuous improvement.</li><li>Take charge of identifying and recommending cost-saving initiatives to reduce operational expenses.</li><li>Responsible for reviewing equipment designs and processes to ensure compliance with safety standards.</li><li>In charge of providing leadership and direction to Technical, Moulding, Equipment, Process Engineers,\nas well as Workplace Safety functions.</li><li>Responsible in monitoring and ensuring environmental validation activities comply with ISO standards, FDA regulations, and other applicable regulatory requirements.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Min Degree in<strong> </strong>Mechanical Engineering.</li><li>Min 8 year of experience in Medical Devices Manufacturing Environment</li><li>Min 5 year of experience in<strong> </strong>leading and delivering complex, technology-driven projects.</li><li>Experience with automation machine design and PLC programming and CNC Machining.</li></ul><p>To submit your application, please apply online to <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com </strong></a>or call +(65) <a href=\"tel:6513 5697\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p><p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p><p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong><br /><strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
